  "prompt": "Are non-living things made up of cells?",
  "response": "No, non-living things are not made up of cells. Cells are the basic structural and functional units of life, found in living organisms. Non-living things are composed of various elements and compounds, but they do not have the cellular structure that characterizes living organisms. For example, rocks, water, and plastic are non-living things that are composed of minerals, molecules, and synthetic materials, respectively, but they do not have cells.",
